%N A396382 A(n,k) read by falling antidiagonals, where A(n,k) is the least positive integer m such that n divides m and k divides m+1; if no such m exists, then A(n,k)=0.
%F A396382 From _Robert Israel_, Jun 24 2026: (Start)
%F A396382 A(n,k) = 0 if GCD(n,k) > 1.
%F A396382 A(n,1) = n.
%F A396382 Otherwise A(n,k) = n * (-n^(-1) mod k). (End)
